# GPTOPT NIP STARTER FILE
# Preset: Visual Quality Baseline
# Status: strategy manifest / not yet validated against a real exported NPI .nip sample

[Profile]
Name=GPTOPT - Visual Quality Baseline
Intent=Prioritize image clarity and quality while keeping performance measurable
Scope=Prefer game-specific profile changes and preserve rollback clarity

[Targets]
TextureFilteringQuality=Quality or High Quality depending on measurable cost
AnisotropicFiltering=Application-controlled or deliberate override where the game benefits clearly
Antialiasing=Prefer application-controlled unless a title-specific override is proven useful
ShaderCache=Enabled
ThreadedOptimization=Auto unless proven harmful by testing
PowerManagement=Normal or game-specific maximum performance only if stutter behavior justifies it
LODApproach=Do not use aggressive negative bias without clear image-quality intent
VRRStrategy=Test with the actual display and sync path in use

[Validation]
Check1=Average FPS
Check2=1 percent low
Check3=Distance clarity changes
Check4=Texture/shimmering behavior
Check5=GPU saturation and frametime cost

[Rollback]
Method=Export the original profile first and only change one image-quality bucket at a time
